Definition: intrusive in a meddling or offensive manner
Example: an interfering old woman; bustling about self-importantly making an officious nuisance of himself; busy about other people's business
Synonyms: meddlesome, noun, attribute, meddlesomeness, meddling, officious, officiousness, busy, busybodied, intrusive, in, a, or, offensive, manner, an, old, woman, bustling, about, self-importantly, making, nuisance, of, himself, other, people, s, business
Category: adj.all
